hpnicfIfExt.name: hpnicfIfExt

revisions.description: The initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfIfExt.description: This MIB is an extension of interface MIBs such as IF-MIB. This MIB is applicable to routers, switches and other products. Some objects in this may be used only for some specific products, so users should refer to the related documents to acquire more detail information.

hpnicfIfHCFlowStatTable.description: This table contains objects to get statistic information of interfaces on a device.

hpnicfRTParentIfTable.name: hpnicfRTParentIfTable
hpnicfRTParentIfTable.description: This table contains all interfaces that can create sub interface.

hpnicfRTParentIfEntry.name: hpnicfRTParentIfEntry
hpnicfRTParentIfEntry.description: This entry describes a interface that can create sub interface.

hpnicfRTParentIfIndex.name: hpnicfRTParentIfIndex
hpnicfRTParentIfIndex.description: The index of interface that can creat sub interface. The value is the same as ifIndex value for this interface.

hpnicfRTMinSubIfOrdinal.name: hpnicfRTMinSubIfOrdinal
hpnicfRTMinSubIfOrdinal.description: The minimum ordinal of the sub interface can be created.

hpnicfRTMaxSubIfOrdinal.name: hpnicfRTMaxSubIfOrdinal
hpnicfRTMaxSubIfOrdinal.description: The max ordinal of the sub interface can be created.

hpnicfRTSubIfTable.name: hpnicfRTSubIfTable
hpnicfRTSubIfTable.description: This table contains objects to create or delete sub interfaces. To create a sub interface, a valid parent interface must be specified by hpnicfRTSubIfParentIfIndex and the hpnicfRTSubIfOrdinal must be in the range between hpnicfRTMinSubIfOrdinal and hpnicfRTMaxSubIfOrdinal of the parent interface from hpnicfRTParentIfTable. Sub interfaces are logical virtual interfaces configured on a main interface. The main interface can be either a physical interface (such as a Layer 3 Ethernet interface) or a logical interface (such as an MFR interface). The subinterfaces on a main interface share the physical layer parameters of the main interface but can have link layer and network layer parameters of their own. Disabling or enabling a subinterface does not affect the main interface, but the main interface status change affects the subinterfaces. The subinterfaces cannot operate normally unless the main interface is connected. A single physical interface containing multiple subinterfaces enables you to network in a more flexible way. You can create subinterfaces for the following physical interfaces: Ethernet interface. An Ethernet subinterface associated with no VLAN supports only IPX, while an Ethernet subinterface associated with a VLAN supports both IP and IPX. WAN interfaces with their data link layer protocols being frame relay, whose subinterfaces support IP and IPX. WAN interfaces with their data link layer protocols being X.25, whose subinterfaces support IP and IPX. ATM interface, whose subinterfaces support only IP.

hpnicfRTSubIfParentIfIndex.name: hpnicfRTSubIfParentIfIndex
hpnicfRTSubIfParentIfIndex.description: The parent interface index. The value should be the same as the hpnicfRTParentIfIndex.

hpnicfRTSubIfOrdinal.name: hpnicfRTSubIfOrdinal
hpnicfRTSubIfOrdinal.description: The ordinal of sub interface. It should between hpnicfRTMinSubIfOrdinal and hpnicfRTMaxSubIfOrdinal of the parent interface.

hpnicfRTSubIfSubIfIndex.name: hpnicfRTSubIfSubIfIndex
hpnicfRTSubIfSubIfIndex.description: The ifIndex value of the sub interface

hpnicfIfLinkModeTable.name: hpnicfIfLinkModeTable
hpnicfIfLinkModeTable.description: This table contains objects to get or set the link mode of an interface. According to the layer at which the device processes received data packets, Ethernet interfaces can operate in bridge or route mode.

hpnicfIfLinkModeEntry.name: hpnicfIfLinkModeEntry
hpnicfIfLinkModeEntry.description: The interface link mode table entry

hpnicfIfLinkModeIndex.name: hpnicfIfLinkModeIndex
hpnicfIfLinkModeIndex.description: The value is same as ifIndex.

hpnicfIfLinkMode.name: hpnicfIfLinkMode
hpnicfIfLinkMode.description: The current link mode of the interface If hpnicfIfLinkModeSwitchSupport is true, writing to the object can change the link mode of the interface.

hpnicfIfLinkModeSwitchSupport.name: hpnicfIfLinkModeSwitchSupport
hpnicfIfLinkModeSwitchSupport.description: Whether the interface supports link mode switching. If this object is true, the interface can operate in either bridge mode or route mode. Otherwise the interfaces can operate only in bridge or route mode.

hpnicfIfPhysicalNumber.name: hpnicfIfPhysicalNumber
hpnicfIfPhysicalNumber.description: Represents the number of physical interfaces in the device.

hpnicfIfTable.name: hpnicfIfTable
hpnicfIfTable.description: A list of interface entries. The number of entries is given by the value of IfNumber.

hpnicfIfEntry.name: hpnicfIfEntry
hpnicfIfEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

hpnicfIfUpDownTimes.name: hpnicfIfUpDownTimes
hpnicfIfUpDownTimes.description: The interface's up/down times, since the device was initialized.

hpnicfIfMtu.name: hpnicfIfMtu
hpnicfIfMtu.description: The size of the largest datagram which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagram, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

hpnicfIfBandwidthRate.name: hpnicfIfBandwidthRate
hpnicfIfBandwidthRate.description: The rate of the bandwidth for an interface.

hpnicfIfDiscardPktRate.name: hpnicfIfDiscardPktRate
hpnicfIfDiscardPktRate.description: The rate of the discarded packets for an interface.

hpnicfIfStatusKeepTime.name: hpnicfIfStatusKeepTime
hpnicfIfStatusKeepTime.description: The time since the interface entered its current operational state.

hpnicfIfInNUcastPkts.name: hpnicfIfInNUcastPkts
hpnicfIfInNUcastPkts.description: The number of non-unicast (i.e., subnetwork- broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

hpnicfIfOutNUcastPkts.name: hpnicfIfOutNUcastPkts
hpnicfIfOutNUcastPkts.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a non- unicast (i.e., a subnetwork-broadcast or subnetwork-multicast) address.

hpnicfIfOperStatus.name: hpnicfIfOperStatus
hpnicfIfOperStatus.description: Current status of the interface. In testing state, no operational packets can be forwarded. If ifAdminStatus is down, hpnicfIfOperStatus should be admindown. If ifAdminStatus is changed to up, hpnicfIfOperStatus should change to up if the interface is ready to send and receive network traffic; otherwise, it should stay in down state.

hpnicfIfDownTimes.name: hpnicfIfDownTimes
hpnicfIfDownTimes.description: Number of times the interface went down, since the device was initialized.

hpnicfIfBandwidthUsageHigh.name: hpnicfIfBandwidthUsageHigh
hpnicfIfBandwidthUsageHigh.description: The notification is generated when the rate of the bandwidth for the interface exceeds the upper limit.

hpnicfIfDiscardPktRateHigh.name: hpnicfIfDiscardPktRateHigh
hpnicfIfDiscardPktRateHigh.description: The notification is generated when the rate of the discarded packets for the interface exceeds the upper limit.

hpnicfIfBandwidthUpperLimit.name: hpnicfIfBandwidthUpperLimit
hpnicfIfBandwidthUpperLimit.description: The rate of the bandwidth upper limit for an interface.

hpnicfIfDiscardPktRateUpperLimit.name: hpnicfIfDiscardPktRateUpperLimit
hpnicfIfDiscardPktRateUpperLimit.description: The rate of the discarded packets upper limit for an interface.
